---
import ProjectLayout from "../../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";

const title = "GymApp 1.0 - Gym Management System [LEGACY / ARCHIVED]";
const description =
  "Monolithic desktop application built with Python and PyQt5 for gym management. A 2021 project that digitized membership management and user check-ins.";
const keywords =
  "python, pyqt5, sqlite, gym management, legacy, desktop app, invoicing";
const author = "Christopher Villamarín";
const applicationName = "GymApp 1.0";
const url = "https://xeland314.github.io/en/projects/gymapp-v1/";
const image = "/images/optimized/projects/gymapp1/imagen1.avif";
const imageAlt = "GymApp 1.0 Preview - User validation";
const robots = "index, follow";
const canonical = "https://xeland314.github.io/en/projects/gymapp-v1/";

const features = [
  {
    title: "Member Management",
    desc: "Registration and validation for active memberships. Check-in control via National ID verification.",
  },
  {
    title: "Billing System",
    desc: "Modules for membership creation, payment tracking, and invoice generation with configurable tax rates.",
  },
  {
    title: "Data Visualization",
    desc: "Physical progress tracking using Matplotlib charts integrated directly into the PyQt5 UI.",
  },
  {
    title: "Local Architecture",
    desc: "Built as a standalone desktop app using SQLite for in-place data persistence.",
  },
];
---

<ProjectLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  keywords={keywords}
  author={author}
  applicationName={applicationName}
  url={url}
  image={image}
  imageAlt={imageAlt}
  robots={robots}
  canonical={canonical}
  lang="en"
>
  <header class="text-center mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black mb-6 tracking-tighter">
      Gym<span
        class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-green-500"
        >App</span
      > 1.0
      <span
        class="text-sm font-normal text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 block mt-2"
        >[LEGACY / ARCHIVED]</span
      >
    </h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Local gym management system developed in 2021. A fundamental step in
      transitioning from manual paperwork to digital operations.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="relative group mb-12">
    <img
      src={image}
      alt={imageAlt}
      class="rounded-2xl shadow-2xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 w-full transform transition group-hover:scale-[1.01]"
    />
  </div>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Key Features</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      {
        features.map((feature) => (
          <div class="group p-8 rounded-2xl bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700 hover:border-blue-500/30 transition-all duration-300 shadow-sm">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
              {feature.title}
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
              {feature.desc}
            </p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Business Narrative</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      This system successfully digitized the operations of local gyms handling
      approximately 50 daily visits (200 total members). The primary goal was to
      reduce membership validation time to <strong>under 10 seconds</strong> using
      a simple ID-based lookup.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Special features included customer loyalty tools, such as birthday alerts
      for targeted discounts, and a flexible inventory system for membership
      types categorized by duration and pricing.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      While functional, the technical and legal landscape has evolved. Looking
      back, the SQLite implementation lacked modern data retention policies and
      the advanced encryption layers that are now standard in my current work.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Technical Architecture</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div
        class="p-6 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/10 rounded-2xl border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800"
      >
        <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 mb-2">
          Tech Stack
        </h4>
        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>• Python 3.x</li>
          <li>• PyQt5 for UI</li>
          <li>• SQLite for Database</li>
          <li>• Matplotlib for plotting</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div
        class="p-6 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/10 rounded-2xl border border-green-200 dark:border-green-800"
      >
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 mb-2">
          Architectural Style
        </h4>
        <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>• Monolithic Application</li>
          <li>• Tight coupling (UI + Logic)</li>
          <li>• Manual State Management</li>
          <li>• Legacy updates (No CI/CD)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Post-Mortem Analysis</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      A creative technical workaround was implemented: <strong
        >Dual Input Support</strong
      >. The system managed two keyboards on a single PC—one for administrative
      tasks and an external numeric keypad for members to check in without
      disrupting the manager's workflow.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      Despite its success, the project lacks a clear separation of concerns,
      with SQL queries often embedded directly within UI views. This project
      remains a milestone in my journey, teaching me the realities of shipping a
      product and handling basic concurrency.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section
    class="mb-12 text-center p-12 rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-600/5 to-gray-500/5 border border-gray-500/10"
  >
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Project Status</h2>
    <p class="mb-8 text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
      This project has been archived and replaced by modern versions compliant
      with current Data Protection Regulations.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
      <span
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl bg-gray-600 text-white font-bold"
      >
        LEGACY / ARCHIVED
      </span>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProjectLayout>
